<paragraph blockId="46.[151,1436,1226,1372]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,326,1226,1252]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Observations:</emphasis>
In a recent phylogenetic study, 
<bibRefCitation author="Abdala" box="[715,887,1226,1252]" firstAuthor="Abdala" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" pagination="1 - 84" refId="ref50199" refString="Abdala, C. S. (2007) Phylogeny of the boulengeri group (Iguania: Liolaemidae, Liolaemus) based on morphological and molecular characters. Zootaxa, 1538, 1 - 84." type="journal article" year="2007">Abdala (2007)</bibRefCitation>
suggested full species status for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cei" authorityYear="1986" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="anomalus" subSpecies="anomalus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">L. anomalus anomalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Abdala 2007: 39)" baseAuthorityName="Abdala" baseAuthorityPageNumber="39" baseAuthorityYear="2007" box="[322,797,1266,1292]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="anomalus" subSpecies="diatadai">
<emphasis box="[322,571,1267,1292]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">L. anomalus diatadai</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Abdala" box="[587,788,1266,1292]" firstAuthor="Abdala" page="39" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" pagination="1 - 84" refId="ref50199" refString="Abdala, C. S. (2007) Phylogeny of the boulengeri group (Iguania: Liolaemidae, Liolaemus) based on morphological and molecular characters. Zootaxa, 1538, 1 - 84." type="journal article" year="2007">Abdala 2007: 39</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Since 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Abdala" authorityYear="2007" box="[882,1027,1267,1292]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="anomalus">
<emphasis box="[882,1027,1267,1292]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">L. anomalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the taxon 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cei" authorityYear="1983" box="[1200,1283,1267,1292]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ditadai">
<emphasis box="[1200,1283,1267,1292]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">ditadai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
exhibit clear patterns of divergence in a series of morphological and coloration traits, we accept 
<bibRefCitation author="Abdala, C. S." box="[1146,1337,1306,1332]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" pagination="1 - 84" refId="ref50199" refString="Abdala, C. S. (2007) Phylogeny of the boulengeri group (Iguania: Liolaemidae, Liolaemus) based on morphological and molecular characters. Zootaxa, 1538, 1 - 84." type="journal article" year="2007">Abdala’s (2007)</bibRefCitation>
suggestions.
</paragraph>
